Cameroon’s President Biya, 51 Others, Eye Election Candidacy

-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 
2011-09-05T14:54:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/cameroonian-president-paul-biya-45-others-seek-candidacy-for-oct-9-vote.html
Cameroonian President Paul Biya and
John Fru Ndi, an opposition-party leader, were among 51 people
who submitted forms to the central African nation’s elections
commission in a bid to contest the presidency on Oct. 9.  The number including candidates who registered at the
Elections Cameroon’s regional offices, Mohaman Sani Tanimou,
head of the commission, told reporters today in Yaounde, the
capital.  In an interview yesterday, Sani Tanimou said three women
were among the group of applicants, whose validity will be
determined by Elections Cameroon by Sept. 20.  Biya, who has led  Africa ’s fourth-biggest cocoa producer
since 1982, was the last to submit the paperwork, Sani Tanimou
said. The campaign period is expected to begin on Sept. 25.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pius Lukong in Yaounde via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 